{
  "stem": "12494.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was-- [SIGHS] there was random-- there were random incursions by-- by all kinds of bands, official, unofficial, German, Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Just-- just people who decided that they wanted to benefit from the situation.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never got caught.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- Of course I was-- I was fortunate in the sense that I immediately had-- immediately, within a week or 10 days-- I had a protective pass that was from my father.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then I went to work for the-- the Jewish Council, the Judenrat, and I had my own protective pass.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at the beginning there was confusion, nobody knew what to do.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it took-- it took weeks until it became clear what the Germans really expected from the Jewish Council.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Fundamentally, the Germans expected from the Jewish Council collaboration, and helping implementing whatever they wanted to do.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was officially called the Jewish Council of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it really wasn't, because not even members of the Jewish Council could travel outside Budapest.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Jews who tried to travel outside Budapest were arrested, put into concentration camps, and deported.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We-- The council was really a Budapest Jewish Council.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It-- and in Budapest, it was expected to cooperate with the Germans, and to provide them with their needs.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And these needs ranged from, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] 1,000 blankets within the next 24 hours for our soldiers to-- particularly apartments, lodging-- for soldiers, SS people, German civilians, all of whom streamed into Hungary and Budapest at that time.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I worked in the lodging department of the Jewish Council.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were fairly highly prized people at the time-- the 48 full members of the Association of Hungarian Jewish University Students.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
